Implement list and query commands.

`chipper list`:
  Show all tickets with priority index, slug, filename, and status.

`chipper top [n]` / `chipper list --top [n]`:
  Show slugs and filenames of the top n active (not done/cancelled/archived) tickets.
  Default n = 5.

`chipper head`:
  Display the full content of the single highest-priority active ticket.

`chipper unsorted` / `chipper list --unsorted`:
  List tickets with a slug but no queue entry.
  Bare command prompts to run interactive sort on each.

`chipper list --unregistered`:
  List ticket files with no slug assigned.

`chipper unregistered`:
  List unregistered files and interactively prompt to assign a slug to each.

`chipper list --orphaned`:
  List slugs or queue entries whose ticket file no longer exists on disk.

`chipper orphaned`:
  List orphaned entries and interactively prompt to relink each to an existing file.

`chipper show <id>`:
  Display the full content of a specific ticket.

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, manifest-implementation
